```
arr = ["The", "quick", "brown", ...];
```
and with the for, you are going through every word, and if you find a word which is bigger than the word longest_word... you consider that word as your longest_word from there on...

@waiswar try this : 
```
function findLongestWord(str) {
  var longest_word = "";
  var arr = str.split(" ");
  for(var i = 0;i <arr.length;i++){
    if(arr[i].length > longest_word.length)
        longest_word = arr[i];    
  }
  return longest_word; // or longest_word.length if you need only the length of the longest word :)
}

findLongestWord('The quick brown fox jumped over the lazy dog');
```

